description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;22.5 Hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The opportunity has arisen to join our small dedicated and supportive team working alongside the Youth offending service to provide mental health assessments and interventions to young people involved in the youth justice system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will get the opportunity to work closely with partner agencies and be part of a wider team to provide a wrap around service to meet the needs of this particular client group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a team we are constantly evolving to meet the needs of the young people we work with and we are looking for someone who can embrace new ideas and be creative in their approach to working with some difficult to engage families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who is confident and can work independently with the support of the wider team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant must be confident in working both remotely and directly with clients and multiple partner agencies across the whole of the Birmingham area.&lt;/p&gt;
